# Lychee link checker exclusion patterns
# Patterns are treated as regular expressions

# ── Placeholder / example URLs ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# These appear in documentation as illustrative examples and are not real sites.
https://your-xmpro-instance\.com
https?://dsserver
https://adfs\.domain\.com
https://mysampleserver
https://xmpro-ad-sample\.azurewebsites\.net

# ── Old GitBook integration catalogue ────────────────────────────────────────
# The XMPro integrations GitBook site has been retired.
# Links are kept for reference but cannot be resolved.
https://xmpro\.gitbook\.io

# ── GitHub Pages for Blueprints / Accelerators / Patterns ───────────────────
# The GitHub Pages site is no longer maintained; individual pattern pages 404.
https://xmpro\.github\.io/Blueprints-Accelerators-Patterns

# ── Private / restricted GitHub repositories ─────────────────────────────────
# The terraform-xmpro-azure repo is private / restricted; CI cannot access it.
https://github\.com/XMPro/terraform-xmpro-azure

# The xmpro-development repo is private / restricted; CI cannot access it.
https://github\.com/XMPro/xmpro-development

# ── External sites that block automated CI requests ──────────────────────────
# McKinsey returns HTTP/2 protocol errors for non-browser user-agents.
https://www\.mckinsey\.com
https://mckinsey\.com

# community.xmpro.com returns network errors for CI bots.
https://community\.xmpro\.com

# Sites that return 403 or timeout for automated requests
https://www\.w3schools\.com
https://portal\.azure\.com
https://courses\.xmpro\.com
https://powerbi\.microsoft\.com
https://azure\.microsoft\.com
https://openai\.com
https://platform\.openai\.com
